Level 0.23, also known as "Half Finished," is a sub-level between [[Level 0]] and [[Level 1]].

=='''Description'''==

Level 0.23 is made up of offices that look as though they are in a factory, with the appearance of the [[Phenomenon 15|Alone]] phenomenon making it so that it is impossible to find any other explorers on the level. The level has a similar design to [[Level 0]]; however, it has scattered windows and appears to be under construction. Some of the windows look out to just a wall, others look out into a bright blue sky that seems to be computer-generated.  

{{Blurimage|file=ventinillas.png|hovertext=Luckily there is nothing in the windows.|caption=A room on the level.}}

Since the level is under construction, there are hazards present, including the collapse of ceilings/floors, ventilation, or lights going out. The perceived height is different for everyone, with some people reporting five floors, others reporting two, and even one. This also affects the perceived dangers; if someone only sees one floor, there would be no possibility of a collapse from the ceiling or floor.

This level appears not to have been disturbed for an extremely long time. It contains open cans, mouldy bread, dust, and various other abandoned objects. It is almost identical to [[Level 0.22]], which leads some explorers to believe that the two levels may have been connected at one point in time but have split for unknown reasons. 

=='''Entities'''==
{{Blurimage|file=1234rrr.png|hovertext=you are just dead meat.|caption=a picture of a cloud.}}
Clouds are something that can be seen outside the windows, floating in the sky. These clouds are exceptionally hostile and invasive. Disturbingly, if you make eye contact for a couple of seconds, they start to distort your very perception in strange, otherworldly ways. For a time, you might find yourself reliving the very best moments of your life— memories flooding your input processor—shadows from the past whispering in your ear; a familiar smell flows around you and reminds you of people, places, long gone, that you felt joy with. Soft, lyrical music might play and stir within you vaguely, a long-ago happening; the longing for something or someone that could be felt or heard from so long ago suddenly returned.

What you don't realize is that this beautiful, remembered moment is a trap for you. While you are entranced by the clouds, all the while your body rots from the inside out. Your lifeforce leaks away slowly, imperceptibly, and with it the world around you warps, distorts, and ultimately fades. The longer you stare at the clouds, the more the grasp on your reality becomes frayed. Eventually, after what feels like an eternity, the last thing you will remember will be the eyes of the clouds, cold, leaking into your perception as they blinked away, and then nothing; no sound, no sensation.

It is theorized that the bodies that are left behind are no longer composed of flesh but instead turn to dust or disappear completely, as if they never existed. 

==Entrances and Exits==

===Entrances===

* Rarely, finding a door on [[Level 0]] labeled "Next Project" will lead you here.

* Entering a building that is under construction on [[Level 11]] or [[Level 111]] will bring one to this level.

* Various unknown factors in [[Level 0.22]] may lead here.

===Exits===

*Going through an exit door will lead you to [[Level 27]] or back to [[Level 0]].

*Various unknown factors may lead back to [[Level 0.22]].

*Finding a hole and falling in may lead to [[level 139]] or [[level 28]].

