''23/5/2003''
I finally figured it out after investing a year studying this level. I can now validate my theory that [[Level 0.22]] was initially connected with Level 0.23. In my search, I saw several indications, paperwork, and other items at the level that authenticate this theory. [[File:AAEGlogo.png|right|188x188px]]
All but one of the signs had images of different sections of each Levels, but connected, and showed how some of the windows would be constructed in [[Level 0.22]]. This is interesting but hard to understand much of as the papers were wet, but they do show this connection nonetheless. But on one of the papers, there was an image of a broken door, and what was behind it was [[the void]]. I don't quite understand what this is trying to say, it doesn't make sense, but what I do understand is that this could be how the levels are formed. Perhaps, all the levels were once in [[Level 0]], and they split off and evolved. For example, [[Level 0]] and [[Level 1]] are marginally similar, perhaps they split off and evolved. The same may apply to [[Level 2]] and [[Level 3]], they are alike and developed similarly. I don't know, it's a pretty far-reaching hypothesis, but I'll still send this to [[A.A.E.G.]].For now I will call this theory [[The Fragmentation Theory|the level fragmentation theory]] and spread it.

